<subSubSection id="9573F20179CC8F8F63C735F34FF2CE24" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C383344DF6A52315B9977F2B9BC1A6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C19DD3F70AA29F469A46047164376E08" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="77029C70E5C4EC9947FCBB1A31C2A5D9" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites seyrigi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis id="3CAABB1BDD3B86D47E85B58D0D5D36D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="8768B5144ACADD83AA103B578E571318" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4ECB5EE34E6DDC006D8F25E8A795D983" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: mesoscutum evenly convex, mostly smooth and shiny, with very fine punctures on anterior part of median lobe (Figs 
<figureCitation id="1B9D58C40647AB8F6119D53DC8474F33" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F9C224387921CC1E02B8805863EB0D64" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13C</figureCitation>
); metapleuron transversely strigose punctate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E89DD41D3530901D256A0333D21A92C7" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6FE9432914A8A630062A215D4FF64B51" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13C</figureCitation>
); juxtacoxal carina strong and complete (Figs 
<figureCitation id="06E7940C2E369C10A7A2B186F8FA7D0C" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EA17F959925B0DED34554B685CC4D984" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13C</figureCitation>
); propodeum strongly rugose; posterior transverse carina forming conspicuous lateral crests in female (Figs 
<figureCitation id="8ED7F768757C180E047AAFA30E4D7239" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (II): A P. nigricollis sp. nov. (holotype) B P. orbitalis sp. nov. (holotype) C P. lineatus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677619" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="AC8A82DD52A57392C8506EE536A8EC8C" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11C</figureCitation>
), lower in male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="57492DFF514C2862E013D91797C026F0" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13C</figureCitation>
); areolet 0.6-0.7
<normalizedToken id="188B3C4BB6D26D99C1B98ED75B2CBA31" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as abscissa of vein 2m-cu above bulla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="74420E117E8227B33AC9E867D59F3E45" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11E</figureCitation>
); front and mid coxae yellow cream, hind coxa black and yellow cream (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E4412146387173B42D8AAF764F3007AC" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1D0EC50B8109B23E9517CCEC4993A039" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Piasites species, habitus of males, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677630" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">12C</figureCitation>
) without longitudinal yellow cream stripe at base; T1 and T3 black, T2 yellow cream (Figs 
<figureCitation id="8E983BC7CB38299C3BC58A42B376A950" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Piasites seyrigi sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum dorsal view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">11A</figureCitation>
12C). Additionally, male has pronotum and mesopleuron mostly smooth and shiny, shallowly strigose punctate dorsally; mesopleuron with shallow rugae close to mesopleural fovea (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1D1858403C1F2FD4EE1596984FFA2596" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="3EF8BF610947F27309B9B6E9D3D8F1B2" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677629" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 11" startId="F11">
