<paragraph id="FBD37F367FF872F6A96EE11BD280E37E" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="C591C773BCBA258449A43ED39A1E4CC3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="DD7467BEB01E4ABC53058F75D5677E8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
In dorsal view, strongly narrowed behind eyes about 0.55 as long as wide. Gena in dorsal view rounded, slightly swollen. Posterior ocellus separated from eye 1.25-1.35
<normalizedToken id="58C4D476A09C6A595A524D84992B6836" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its maximum diameter. Distance between posterior ocelli 1.0-1.2
<normalizedToken id="282571BC16EC407D068D3C3FB611ACC3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their diameter. Occipital carina complete, evenly curved in dorsal view. Face mostly smooth and shiny, slightly convex in the central part, with very fine setiferous punctures. Clypeal suture present laterally. Clypeus 1.80-1.95
<normalizedToken id="2C6675CFD972349CC696FD81C6A59F06" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as medially long, very convex, with relatively long setae in the central part, prominent in lateral view, ventral margin slightly rounded, almost truncate, with a weak median denticle. Malar space 0.6-0.7
<normalizedToken id="FF97503F09A56CBF4F8253FE4535549D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basal mandibular width. Mandible 1.55
<normalizedToken id="D61A436B12CCFE268DF3C544B4F61170" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basal width; dorsal tooth distinctly longer than ventral one. Antenna with 29 flagellomeres, strongly tapered towards apex; flagellomeres from f10(11) to apex conspicuously flattened ventrally; f1 7.0-7.5
<normalizedToken id="5323F74028374F5B1064EA11BAB23F82" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as its maximum width.
</paragraph>
<caption id="ADA32BB6B9752873847854360CE0E9E9" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 13" startId="F13">
